Eth api using baseFee only when needed (#1818)

The Problem
The eth RPC API after expreso required some amending.

On ethereum, baseFee ( called gasPriceMinimun on Celo) is present on the block header. For Celo, it's present on the GasPriceMinimum contract, and it also needs to be denominated in all different fee currencies.

This difference poses a problem on the RPC, since whenever a Transaction or a TransactionReceipt is constructed, the gasPrice field is computed for new transaction. To do so, it uses the baseFee. Obtaining the baseFee for block X is easy on Ethereum and hard on Celo; since it's a smart contract call, the node needs to have the state available but that's not true for historical blocks on any node that it's not an archive node.

The Solution
To solve this issue, this PR takes the following approach:

If node has access to the block's state, then gasPrice is computed as usual
If node doesn't have access to block's state, then gasPrice is nil
Additionally, we have the same problem with the new AccessList rpc endpoint, that computes the access list for a transaction on a given block. If the block is too old, and we don't have the state, then the rpc will fail.

Return no effectiveGasPrice instead of 0 (#1825)

If the state is not available to calculate the effectiveGasPrice then
don't return the field.

Refactor source params into separate object

We had a lot variables that we had to pass down from the project view,
and only very few where important to the reactivity of the components.

By using the resolved Promise from `getProject` as transport we can use
now the `source` variable and get the required params by destructuring
it.

In short we can pack now the following params:
```
urn, org, user, seed, peer, project, branches, peers, config, anchors
```

Use SHA256 when dealing with P2WSH script

According to [BIP141](https://github.com/bitcoin/bips/blob/master/bip-0141.mediawiki#p2wsh)
all operations around the P2WSH script should
use SHA256. In our context, that means we should
use this hashing when building deposit
transactions and during deposit reveal,
specifically while performing expected
script hash validation. Initially, we were using
HASH256 (double SHA256) by mistake and were
producing P2WSH transaction which could not be
unlocked by the sweeping wallet. This changeset
fixes this mistake.

NNS1-937: Add checks for registry version invariants

This change ensures the following invariants on the registry's changelog versions are enforced in the post-upgrade hook (a panic occurs otherwise):
* That the registry's first version is version 1
* The the sequence of versions is continuous
* That the last version never moves back after an upgrade

[OR-59] Make RegistryReplicator take node_id optionally

RegistryReplicator takes node_id to check if the current node is becoming an NNS node, in case of an NNS switch-over.

A boundary node will never be a member of a subnet that is taking over NNS. Therefore, we can start RegistryReplicator without a node_id on boundary nodes. Therefore, this MR makes node_id optional.

api: Set some default profiles to streams (#875)

* api: Set some default profiles in case none specified

It's kind of a roadblock for initial developers trying to test
Livepeer to be obliged to provide transcoding profiles for the
stream, especially when they might not even know how to configure
those.

When I went through it, I actually went on the dashboard and open
the developer network tab to find out what the dashboard was setting
when creating a stream from the UI, since from there, there is no
requirement for configuring anything.

With this change, it becomes simpler for API users as well, while
still maintaining retro-compatibility and allowing to configure the
profiles manually if desired.
